title: Ion Images, Key Parameters, IMAGE Extreme UltraViolet (EUV) experiment - Bill Sandel (U/Arizona)

info.x_cadence_note: Counts based on variable 'Epoch' in https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/sp_phys/data/image/euv/euv_k0/2000/im_k0_euv_20000328_v01.cdf. The most common cadence occurred for 5.2632% of the 2 timesteps. Cadence = 600180 [ms] = PT10M0.18S.

parameters.name: IMAGE
parameters.description: EUV ion (He+) images of earth and surrounding plasmasphere (no grid, small format, linear scale)

parameters.name: IMAGE_LT
parameters.description: ---> EUV ion images, as above (large format). This variable is a 'virtual' variable that is computed using the function alternate_view (see https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/pub/software/cdawlib/source/virtual_funcs.pro) on the with inputs of the variables ['IMAGE']. Note that some COMPONENTS may not be available from the HAPI interface. They are accessible from the raw CDF files, however.

parameters.name: IMAGE_MV
parameters.description: ---> EUV ion images, as above (movie). parameters.name: IMAGE_LOG
parameters.description: ---> EUV ion images, as above (log10 scale). This variable is a 'virtual' variable that is computed using the function convert_log10 (see https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/pub/software/cdawlib/source/virtual_funcs.pro) on the with inputs of the variables ['IMAGE'].
